;B[gd]LB[cd:1][eb:2][gd:3]CR[ge]C[Dia.1 Solid Defense

This is a shape that we learned in our session on jeongseok.  Black should definitely solidly defend with 1, it's a good move.  The tiger's mouth of White 2 is solid shape.  Up to here is jeongseok, but since Black gets to play 3 he's really happy because White cannot make use of the marked stone.
\lang1042\f1\fs18
