;W[ff]LB[db:1][ec:2][bb:3][cd:4][bc:5][de:6][ed:7][ff:8]CR[cb]C[Dia.4 Crosscut

In response to the marked White stone Black can play at 1 and 3 to capture the stone but this is just what White is waiting for.  White can cut through Black's shape with 4.  Black connects at 5 and now White can play at 6 and then cut at 8.

What do you think?  This is pretty complicated.  The upshot is White is going either capture one or two stones, so he is going to have a nice shape on the outside.
\lang1042\f1\fs18
